 \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"aa07212d0dea0e6db20438c4b57f5b3aacc40bb6527b7b1a8d678f1c6c04fbbe","event_uuid":"636c2b46-b2ed-4b14-9eb5-3cb9012eb982","position":{"commit_sha":"9a1b04b4d10e3efc7acce19c739bbda178e7a902","position":"1784401803126107657-636c2b46-b2ed-4b14-9eb5-3cb9012eb982"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"e1dc6410-25d7-406a-b015-01c40c9fa16a","comments":[],"created_at":1784397382173494001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Goal\nGraduate `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile.py` (currently 1093 LOC, the single LARGEST module-size offender) off the module-size gate by extracting a cohesive cluster of 10 pure/IO leaf UTILITY symbols into a NEW sibling leaf module `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile_helpers.py`.\n\n## Seam (on the code's CURRENT structure)\nThe 10 moved symbols are the pass's leaf support utilities — NONE take `_PassContext`; they are pure/IO helpers the staying `_PassContext`-driven phase helpers call: `StatusMappingError`, `preflight_status_mapping`, `_commit_binding_store_snapshot`, `_audit_log_probe`, `route_inbound_probe`, `_read_local_tickets`, `_build_filter_target_set`, `_mutation_matches_filter`, `_build_plan_entries`, `_NoOpSyncLogger` (~412 LOC of bodies). The leaf reproduces the `lazy_load`+`_load` bootstrap boilerplate (same pattern as sibling `run_differs.py`) so it lazy-loads ITS OWN siblings (config.py, alert_store.py, mutation.py, inbound_probe.py, git_adapter). The leaf imports NOTHING from reconcile.py (true leaf, no back-edge). reconcile.py loads the leaf immediately AFTER the `_load` helper is defined (post lazy_load bootstrap, ~current line 266) via `_helpers = _load('reconcile_helpers', 'reconcile_helpers.py')`, then binds each of the 10 names as a module-level re-export.\n\n## Stale-comment updates in scope (BOTH files)\nTwo now-stale in-tree assertions about route_inbound_probe's residency are updated as part of this change:\n1. reconcile.py comment near current line 586 (contains 'route_inbound_probe stays here because it is a separately-tested public surface') -> replaced with prose stating route_inbound_probe now lives in the reconcile_helpers.py leaf and is re-exported here (reconcile_once still passes the re-exported bare name into run_differs).\n2. run_differs.py module docstring (current lines ~15-17), which contains 'which reconcile.py keeps because it is a separately-tested public surface' -> replaced with prose saying route_inbound_probe now lives in reconcile_helpers.py and is re-exported FROM reconcile.py. The parameter-passing design (run_differs holds no back-edge; the router is passed in, not imported) is UNCHANGED — only the residency clause is corrected.\n\n## DEVIATION from docs/architecture.md remedy row (stated plainly)\nThe arch.md offenders-table row for reconcile.py proposes a `reconcile_passes.py` seam extracting the `_PassContext`-driven pass-phase helpers (`_load_snapshots`/`_handle_corrupt_snapshot`/`_apply_mutations`/`_persist_and_log`). That row is SUPERSEDED: that seam would need THREE modules to avoid a back-edge, because those phase helpers depend on the leaf utilities extracted here — so the phase helpers cannot move cleanly without dragging the utilities along or importing back into reconcile.py. Leaf-utility extraction is the cleaner single split. This ticket DELETES the stale reconcile.py remedy row from docs/architecture.md.\n\n## Nature of change\nA pure/mechanical refactor (move + re-export; the only prose edits are the two stale-comment corrections above; no signature or logic changes). E5 testing-plan is not-applicable — the existing reconciler unit tests are the oracle (many load reconcile.py by-path and access these symbols as `reconcile.<symbol>` attributes, which the re-exports preserve).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] New leaf `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile_helpers.py` exists and is in [100,800] LOC. Verified by: `n=$(wc -l < src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile_helpers.py); [ \"$n\" -ge 100 ] && [ \"$n\" -le 800 ]` exits 0 (expected ~497).\n- [ ] `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile.py` is <=800 LOC. Verified by: `[ \"$(wc -l < src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile.py)\" -le 800 ]` exits 0 (expected ~685).\n- [ ] reconcile.py removed from the module-size gate files and its remedy row deleted from docs. Verified by: `grep -c 'reconcile.py' .github/module-size-allowlist.txt` returns 0, `grep -c 'rebar_reconciler/reconcile.py ' .github/module-size-ceilings.txt` returns 0, and `grep -c 'rebar_reconciler/reconcile.py' docs/architecture.md` returns 0.\n- [ ] reconcile_helpers.py is NOT added to either gate file. Verified by: `grep -c reconcile_helpers .github/module-size-allowlist.txt .github/module-size-ceilings.txt` returns 0 for both.\n- [ ] The two stale route_inbound_probe residency comments are replaced in BOTH files. Verified by: `grep -c 'route_inbound_probe stays here' src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile.py` returns 0 AND `grep -c 'reconcile.py keeps' src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/run_differs.py` returns 0.\n- [ ] The module-size contract test passes. Verified by: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q` exits 0.\n- [ ] All 10 symbols remain resolvable as `reconcile.<symbol>` via re-export and the reconciler unit suite is green. Verified by: `python -m pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler -q` exits 0.\n- [ ] Lint is clean. Verified by: `make lint` prints 'All checks passed!' and exits 0.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile_helpers.py","reason":"NEW leaf module holding the 10 extracted pass leaf-utility symbols (~475 LOC)"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile.py","reason":"remove the 10 moved bodies; add the _helpers=_load(...) block + re-export bindings (1093 -> ~685 LOC)"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/run_differs.py","reason":"update the module docstring (lines ~15-17) whose route_inbound_probe residency assertion goes stale after the move"},{"path":".github/module-size-allowlist.txt","reason":"remove reconcile.py bare-path row (graduated under 800)"},{"path":".github/module-size-ceilings.txt","reason":"remove reconcile.py <path> <max> ceiling row"},{"path":"docs/architecture.md","reason":"delete the stale reconcile.py offenders-table remedy row (reconcile_passes.py seam superseded by this leaf-utility split)"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","716f-b917-9fc8-41f5"]],"parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","parent_status_uuid":"8af317a7-a8ab-4fe1-9d99-98dddc0318da","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":1,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["module-size"],"ticket_id":"3c7f-bd5d-3d79-40f7","ticket_type":"story","title":"Split reconcile.py — extract pass leaf utilities into reconcile_helpers.py (graduate off module-size gate)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["b5e68360-c9e5-4c9a-9287-f65c8a4dc69f","c73a9442-eff0-44c4-9847-76d49d4564b6","ad441435-c30f-4a4a-a925-5cb304866388","60e3ffe5-d820-4e25-95a8-a0ca79341393","81c8ef54-2b6a-45da-9e02-af5d098e1e70","4c2e551e-a227-40c5-b0c2-afb00bc00665","5f8768e3-06e1-4188-9a98-3a42881e4af9","1deb4214-73ce-412c-b166-74897a038104","272271dd-db9a-4414-b1e8-59e39cf7ae76","8af317a7-a8ab-4fe1-9d99-98dddc0318da","674ca531-50bb-465d-9d0c-da9043f06d99","636c2b46-b2ed-4b14-9eb5-3cb9012eb982"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784401803126107658,"uuid":"07267b99-b45d-4abd-82d4-f0e4b84defe7"}